An e-bike rider was killed when he slammed into a pole on the Upper East Side early Monday, cops said. The man was heading south in the bike lane on Second Avenue near East 89th Street around 12:40 a.m. when he lost control and struck a pole on the sidewalk, police said. He suffered head trauma and was rushed to Weill Cornell Medical Center, where he was pronounced dead, authorities said. The cyclistâ€™s identity was not immediately known. No other vehicles were involved in the crash.